{"key":"processedPost-8477581","value":{"id":8477581,"first":8417671,"last":8484670,"when":1212469651,"utime":"06/03/08 08:07 AM","content":"Keep your dishes in a stack, right side up, and condensation won't be a problem.  Next time, let the agar cool longer before pouring.  Storing upside down will cause the moisture from the agar to drop from gravity to the lid, drying out your culture.  When you turn it over to get the culture out, the water splashes down and floods your mycelium.<br />RR","title":"Re: Standing water on agar"}}